val vernacular English form of   Cecilia ."],"variants":[{"name":"Cecilie","meanings":["Medieval vernacular English form of   Cecilia ."]},{"name":"Cicely","meanings":["Variant of   Cecily .  This was a common form of the name in the Middle Ages, and in the 20th century was well known as the name of the British actress and singer  Cicely Courtneidge  (  1893–1980 )."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":33,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":42,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Cecily de Waleton was born on 1 November 1181, in Walton on the Hill, Lancashire, England, her father, Henry de Waleton, was 30 and her mother, Juliana of Halewood, was 26. She married Alan de Columbers about 1200. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1230, in Halewood, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 49, and was buried in Preston, Lancashire, England."},"et":{"1 November 1181–1230":"1. november 1181–1230","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1181–1230":"1181–1230","–1246":"–1246","–1262":"–1262","1177–1235":"1177–1235","1201–1298":"1201–1298","1151–1199":"1151–1199","1155–1181":"1